The paper deals with a combinatorial optimization problem on hypergraphs, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity) categories. The problem involves finding a minimum-weight vertex multiset, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) categories. Finally, the paper presents a bi-approximation algorithm, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category.
